cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.AC, cs.SC 

The paper deals with polynomial identity testing (PIT) and its implications for algebraic complexity theory. Specifically, it gives an explicit version of Noether's Normalization lemma for the ring of invariants of matrices under simultaneous conjugation, which has implications for PIT algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CC (Computational Complexity), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper also discusses algebraic circuits (cs.AC) and parallel algorithms (cs.SC), which further support these sub-categories.
